  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering at both national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Wolfsberg Principles\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- United States Bank Secrecy Act\n- European Union Anti-Money Laundering Directives\n- UK Proceeds of Crime Act\n- Many countries have specific anti-money laundering (AML) regulations\n\n3. Key Components:\n- Customer due diligence requirements\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Enhanced monitoring of high-risk transactions\n- Mandatory record-keeping\n- International cooperation between law enforcement agencies\n\n4. Regulatory Mechanisms:\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n- Transaction monitoring systems\n- Mandatory financial institution reporting\n- Criminal penalties for non-compliance\n\n5. Enforcement:\n- Financial institutions required to implement compliance programs\n- Regular audits and inspections\n- Significant financial penalties for violations\n- Criminal prosecution for serious offenses\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different sectors and jurisdictions.",
